{
  "stem": "20021.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And of course, lessons in mathematics was-- and biology, in particular, was Yiddish as the language of instructions really funny, was really [? difficult. ?]",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, next after the Germans [? ran ?] over the Russian part, I found myself suddenly under Hitler.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my immediate decision was I go back to Tarnow because--",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was with my brother-- my brother.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we were able to correspond because it was just one country.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So the mails were going out.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It took a week for every letter, two weeks for a letter to reach and be exchanged, but it was possible to communicate by letter.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "With my mother.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So obviously, my mother had a job.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The apartment which our apartment was divided into three apartments, three different families lived there, but she still had the living room, which was the major part and the kitchen.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So the kitchen was shared by all the three families.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And she had a job and we-- she believed that she can get work for us, too.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The question was just how to get from there to Tarnow.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And this was like a distance of 200 kilometers.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Jews were not allowed to travel already by train, already at that time, by train or by bus or by this.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So in a way, that was a difficulty.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But we managed to overcome this difficulty, kind of smuggled ourselves through-- back to Tarnow.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we got papers had to be arranged because the-- there was at that point-- Tarnow was ruled by Judenrat, which meant the Germans appointed a Jewish commission which sort of ruled the town.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they had their own police, Jewish policemen.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So they didn't have weapons, but they had sticks.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
